  "text": "We have previously addressed the issue of autofluorescence using rhodamine (red) anti-GFP antibodies to determine whether green fluorescing cells were expressing GFP protein or were examples of autofluorescence. In summary, under the conditions of our experiments, autofluorescence was rare or not seen and if present was excluded from the counts by use of the double bandpass filter [CITATION_1] . The geographical location of the GFP positive cells is shown in Figure 5 . Donor hematopoietic cells (GFP+CD45+) , host hematopoietic cells (GFP-CD45+) and donor cells with a nonhematopoietic phenotype (GFP+CD45-) are seen distributed at different locations in the alveolar walls.",
